    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-12T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-12T04:00:00-05:00" n="215"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d215">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Moscow/257: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HWA2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-12T12:00:00+03:00"
                            >November 12, 1943—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1925. Secret and personal for the Secretary from the Ambassador.</p>
                <p>Reference your 1180 November 9,<note n="1" xml:id="d215fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_171">p. 171</ref>.</note> as
                    authorized by the Department I have had my letter of Nov. 10 to <persName
                        corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> containing the President’s agreement
                    concerning Turkey attached as an annex to the Soviet-British protocol concerning
                    Turkey signed by <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> on November 1 in Moscow.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d215fn2">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_148">p.
                            148</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Since <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> finally decided that the
                    above arrangement was preferable I did not insist on the protocol and annex
                    being incorporated in the secret military record of the conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HWA2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
